<TITLE> S Africa govt says power cuts a `national emergency' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pretoria, Jan 25 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - South Africa's rolling power cuts are a "national emergency" but economic growth can continue at healthy levels if energy is used more efficiently, Public Enterprises Minister Alec Erwin said on Friday. "It is clear that we are running our power system at utilisation levels that are overstretching maintanance," Erwin told reporters in a briefing in Pretoria, according to SAPA news agency. Erwin said the economy, which has boomed in recent years, could continue to grow at healthy rates "if we change our behaviour and become more energy efficient.
